<h2 id="head-8fb937b602b4f2ef21c7fab00ac15de3b3ba49ea">Discussion</h2>
<p>
Johenius:  Is using floor inscriptions considered cheating? I've seen a few DitL'ers using them, but always considered it a bit scummy... 
</p>
<p>
<strong>ZV</strong>:Why, no. They're not too powerful, it ain't very easy to get them, not every grid has enough mana to use them and it can be bothersome to type them (yeah, I know, macros). 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Remember also that using an inscription takes a lot of time (e.g. 3 rounds for a character with speed 0). 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./HarryErwin">HarryErwin</a></strong>: Is there any reason to keep the parchments? 
</p>

    <ul>

 <a href="./VelKrov">VelKrov</a>: None. Just be sure to read them. 
    </ul>


